<TITLE> Six powers ask EU to continue Iran diplomacy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 United Nations, March 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The five permanent UN Security Council members and Germany want the EU's foreign policy chief to meet Iran's chief nuclear negotiator to try to resolve a nuclear impasse with Tehran, Britain said on Monday. British UN ambassador John Sawers said this in a statement to the UN Security Council he read on behalf of Britain, France, United States, China, Russia and Germany after the council imposed a third round of sanctions on Iran for refusing to suspend sensitive parts of its nuclear program. The EU foreign policy chief is Javier Solana, who has represented the six powers since they made an offer of incentives to Iran in 2006 on condition that Tehran would freeze all sensitive nuclear activities
